short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 127}, "passed": true}}, "text": "2. INCREASED ARAB NAVAL ACTIVITY IN RED SEA AREA\n\nThree of Egypt's four destroyers, the\nNasr, Qaher and Fateh, were scheduled\nto transit south through the Suez Canal\n\nThe United States naval attaché in Cairo\nhas reported that the ships were to carry\nEgyptian naval cadets on a visit to unspeci-\nfied ports.\n\nthe ships may make \"good-will\" visits to\nthe Sudanese port of Port Sudan and to the\nSaudi port of Jidda.\n\nThese vessels are superior in gun power\nto the two Israeli patrol escorts stationed at Eilat. The Nasr\nis one of two modern Soviet-built ships acquired in 1956. Egypt\nis not believed to have succeeded in obtaining ammunition for the\nmain batteries of the Qaher and Fateh, which were purchased\nfrom Britain last year", "token_count": 127, "token_end_0based": 126, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "2 increased arab naval activity in red sea area three of egypt's four destroyers the nasr qaher and fateh were scheduled to transit south through the suez canal the united states naval attach in cairo has reported that the ships were to carry egyptian naval cadets on a visit to unspeci fied ports the ships may make good-will visits to the sudanese port of port sudan and to the saudi port of jidda these vessels are superior in gun power to the two israeli patrol escorts stationed at eilat the nasr is one of two modern soviet-built ships acquired in 1956 egypt is not believed to have succeeded in obtaining ammunition for the main batteries of the qaher and fateh which were purchased from britain last year", "unred_source_page": 5}
